@startuml
title UML state machine diagram

[*] --> S1 : [initial state]
state S1 <<initial>>
state Order
Order : entry/plane is newly acquired
Order : do/plane is in order state
Order : exit/plane is delivered

state Arrival
Arrival : entry/plane arrives
Arrival : do/plane transitions to preparation

state Preparation
Preparation : entry/plane is prepared
Preparation : do/plane is ready for operations or maintenance

state Operations
Operations : entry/plane is in operations
Operations : do/plane is used for scheduled flights
Operations : exit/plane is sent to maintenance if no more flights

state Maintenance
Maintenance : entry/plane is in maintenance
Maintenance : do/plane is serviced and checked
Maintenance : exit/plane is prepared for operations

state OutOfService
OutOfService : entry/plane is no longer available for use
OutOfService : do/plane is taken out of service

state Removed
Removed : entry/plane is permanently withdrawn from service
Removed : do/plane is removed from operations

S1 --> Order
Order --> Arrival
Arrival --> Preparation
Preparation --> Operations
Operations --> Maintenance
Maintenance --> Preparation
Preparation --> OutOfService
OutOfService --> Removed

[*] --> Removed : [final state]

@enduml
